      </TD><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="35%"><H2>1. hedging</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="55%"><P>a. the condition where the forward rate of a currency is more than the spot rate by the same percentage that its interest rate is lower than the other country's interest rate.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_2" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>2. speculating</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>b. the act of reducing or eliminating a net asset or net liability position in the foreign currency.</TD></TR>


