	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_4" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>4. covered international investment</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>d. when the exchange rate at which anticipated investment returns will be redeemed is not determined until the trade occurs at the future spot rate.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_5" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>5. uncovered international investment</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>e. an agreement to exchange one currency for another on some date in the future at the forward exchange rate.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_6" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>6. covered interest differential</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>f. when the exchange rate at which anticipated foreign investment returns will be redeemed is determined in the present through a forward contract.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_7" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>7. forward premium</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>g. a net liability position</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_8" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>8. long position</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>h. the act of taking a net asset position or a net liability position in some foreign currency.</TD></TR>


	<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2><INPUT TYPE=TEXT NAME="Q17_9" SIZE=3></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><H2>9. short position</TD><TD VALIGN=TOP><P>i. the difference between the rate of returns from investing money in the US at the market rate of interest or participating in the spot and forward markets for U.S. dollars and another currency.</TD></TR>


